Hook on ischium of third pereiopod only; hook long, overreaching basioischial articulation, not opposed by tubercle on basis. First pleopods of form I male symmetrical and continuous at bases (Fig. 
2I
), extending to midpoint of bases of third pereiopods when abdomen flexed. First pleopod of form I male as described in Diagnosis but with distal half of mesial process directed caudolaterally approximately 15 degrees, proximal edge at 90 degree angle to main axis of the pleopod. (
Fig. 1J
).

Color
.— Base color of dorsal and lateral surfaces of chelae, cephalothorax, abdomen, pereiopods, and tail fan rather uniform and light to dark brown (
Fig. 3
). Dorsal surface of abdominal segments 1 through 5 usually darker brown than base color, giving the appearance of dark wedge running down center of dorsum. Pleurites of first abdominal segment cream colored. Tubercles on chelae and spines on carpus light orange or cream colored. Rostral margins orange or crimson red (
Fig. 3
). Faint U­shaped saddle centered at caudal edge of cephalothorax and extending cephalically may be present on individuals with light brown base color. Ventral surfaces of chelae, cephalothorax, and abdomen cream to white.
